metadata.name: Master & The Mountain
metadata.description:
Kenji Matsuda began exploring his Ainu roots when he moved to Lake Akan Onsen, Hokkaido in his early 20â€™s. He eventually became a community leader and is now the chairman of the Akan Ainu Culture Preservation Society. In this photo he is wearing traditional Ainu clothing and facing Pennishiri - the mountain that overlooks Lake Akan and is revered in Ainu culture.

This photo has appeared as a double page spread in National Geographic Traveler, China.
